interpreter_output.explicit_intent:
Return one numeric scalar: the ratio = COUNT(customers where currency = 'EUR') / COUNT(customers where currency = 'CZK'). Use the customers table only (no transaction joins). Example SQL patterns: 
1) Standard SQL: SELECT CAST(SUM(CASE WHEN currency = 'EUR' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) AS FLOAT) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN currency = 'CZK' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END), 0) AS eur_to_czk_ratio FROM customers;
2) PostgreSQL: SELECT (COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE currency = 'EUR'))::float / NULLIF(COUNT(*) FILTER (WHERE currency = 'CZK'), 0) AS eur_to_czk_ratio FROM customers;
Notes: do not GROUP BY (single scalar). Handle division-by-zero with NULLIF (returns NULL if no CZK customers). Cast to float to get non-integer ratio.
